GoalDesc: Protect, restore and promote sustainable use of terrestrial ecosystems, sustainably manage forests, combat desertification, and halt and reverse land degradation and halt biodiversity loss
TargetDesc: Promote fair and equitable sharing of the benefits arising from the utilization of genetic resources and promote appropriate access to such resources, as internationally agreed
IndicatorDesc: Number of countries that have adopted legislative, administrative and policy frameworks to ensure fair and equitable sharing of benefits
SeriesDesc: Countries that are contracting Parties to the International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture (PGRFA) (1 = YES; 0 = NO)
Source: https://www.cbd.int/abs/nagoya-protocol/signatories/default.shtml, Access and Benefit-sharing Clearing-house https://absch.cbd.int/, http://www.fao.org/plant-treaty/countries/membership/en/,  The Online Reporting System on Compliance of the International Treaty on PGRFA http://faoitpgrfa.ort-production.linode.unep-wcmc.org and  Easy-SMTA https://mls.planttreaty.org ,
Footnotes: Parties  refers to Contracting Parties to the International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture that have ratified, accepted, approved or acceded this instrument, including those for which the Treaty has not yet entered into force following the 90 days period set out in Article 28.1  of the Treaty. For values:  TRUE = 1.0; FALSE = 0.0.  Data as of 1 January 2017.

IndicatorDesc: Number of countries that have adopted legislative, administrative and policy frameworks to ensure fair and equitable sharing of benefits
SeriesDesc: Countries that are contracting Parties to the International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture (PGRFA) (1 = YES; 0 = NO)
Source: https://www.cbd.int/abs/nagoya-protocol/signatories/default.shtml, Access and Benefit-sharing Clearing-house https://absch.cbd.int/, http://www.fao.org/plant-treaty/countries/membership/en/,  The Online Reporting System on Compliance of the International Treaty on PGRFA http://faoitpgrfa.ort-production.linode.unep-wcmc.org and  Easy-SMTA https://mls.planttreaty.org ,
Footnotes: Parties  refers to Contracting Parties to the International Treaty on Plant Genetic Resources for Food and Agriculture that have ratified, accepted, approved or acceded this instrument, including those for which the Treaty has not yet entered into force following the 90 days period set out in Article 28.1  of the Treaty. For values:  TRUE = 1.0; FALSE = 0.0.  Data as of 1 January 2017.
